<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5278] groovy allows top-level classes be marked as private</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5278</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Groovy allows to make a class like this: private class X{}.&lt;br/&gt;
The result is a top level class, that will be having the private modifier set. But the JVM spec does not include this modifier in the allowed modifiers for classes. Instead this modifier is supposed to be a reserved flag for future use. The violation of this causes internal errors when using indy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
