                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14472442" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 6 Feb 2012 04:19:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I reduced the priority a bit because I found it was not this, that causes the indy internal error. The same issue happens with package scoped classes. Also those private classes are quite a bit in use it seems. It would maybe be better to provide an implementation for example as static inner class or such&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472464" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 13 Feb 2012 05:09:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;we decided to make it fail at compilation for now&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472479" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 14 Feb 2012 07:55:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I implemented the compiler check, which will now throw an exception if it encounters a private top level class&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
